        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Controller_Front::dispatch() does not render response's exceptions, even if I set response's renderException flag to TRUE.\n\n{code}$response = new Zend_Controller_Response_Http();\n$response->setException(new Exception('My message...'));\n$response->renderExceptions(true);\n\n$front = Zend_Controller_Front::getInstance();\n$front->setResponse($response);\n...\n$front->dispatch();{code}\n\nAt the end of dispatch the front controller sends response with sendHeaders() and outputBody() methods, but response object renders exceptions only through sendResponse() method.\n\nI don't understand why front controller sends response this way, a call to sendResponse() or a simple echo should do the work.\nI think the response object should decide alone how to handle exceptions.\n"
        },
